headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 33 points and the NBA-leading Boston Celtics won their eighth straight game, beating the short-handed Detroit Pistons 129-102 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaylen Brown scores 33 points, NBA-leading Celtics beat Pistons 129-102 for 8th straight win

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 23 points in his only regular-season trip to his homeland, Chet Holmgren had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and the Oklahoma City Thunder pulled away late to beat the short-handed Toronto Raptors 123-103 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 23 as Thunder win 4th straight, hand Raptors 9th consecutive loss

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — The New Orleans Pelicans had quite a rebuttal.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum scores 30 as Pelicans add to Heat's home woes with 111-88 win

headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves top Cavaliers 104-91 behind Conley's 21 points and fan favorite Reid's 18

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 28 points, including the winning basket with 1.2 seconds left, and the undermanned Memphis Grizzlies overcame 31 points and 16 rebounds from Victor Wembanyama to snap a four-game skid with a 99-97 win over the San Antonio...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson scores 28, including winner in final seconds, as Grizzlies top Wembanyama, Spurs, 99-97

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 26 points and had 11 assists, Pascal Siakam added 25 points and grabbed 16 rebounds and the Indiana Pacers beat the Golden State Warriors 123-111 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton and Siakam lead Pacers past Warriors 123-111

events.name: LA Clippers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 31 points, Kawhi Leonard had 22 and the Los Angeles Clippers swept a two-game set in Portland, beating the Trail Blazers 125-117 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers sweep 2-game set in Portland, beating the Trail Blazers 125-117

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 23 points and 19 rebounds, and D’Angelo Russell set the Lakers record for 3-pointers in a single season during Los Angeles' 101-94 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis, LeBron James lead 4th-quarter charge as the Lakers hold off Philadelphia 101-94
